cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.FL, cs.AI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with formal grammars and their application to natural language processing. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses the link between the categorical viewpoint on natural language and probabilistic language models, which is a common topic in machine learning. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper discusses automata and their construction from formal grammars. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is relevant as the paper deals with formal grammars and their application to automata. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the application of formal grammars to natural language processing, which is a common topic in AI research.
